<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-06-28T16:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-06-28T16:30:00-05:00" n="8" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d8">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">810.24/42: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Scott</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-28T17:00:00-04:30">June 28,
                                    1939—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 6:16 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>57. Department’s instruction of June 27, 7 p.m. The Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs states that his Government cannot express an opinion until it
                            has had time to study the exact copy of the proposed legislation. If the
                            Department will kindly forward same by air mail I will endeavor to
                            obtain an expression of opinion as quickly as possible.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Scott</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>